<br>
Cassea, druids have a lot going for them, and haven't fared as badly as some would suggest. Off the top of my head, recent improvements to the class:<br>
<br>
Moonfire.v2 - How much does this damage over our lower levelr spells ratio wise?<br>
<br>
Spirit of Eagle - Nothing but Lev and SOW and See Invis in one spell<br>
<br>
AC/ATK/FR debuffs - Two spells combined into one<br>
<br>
Circle of Seasons - Two spells combined into one<br>
<br>
PotC quest, and 2 nice earrings - This is a single cast version of a spell that we should have gotten from day one. I will agree that POTG was a nice spell but they had to go and ruin it by making it have stacking issues. Why do the Druid buffs always seem to have stacking issues in which other class spells do not stack with our buffs?<br>
<br>
Nature's Recovery.v2 (hopefully we'll see v3) - Same mana / ratio as lower level heal<br>
<br>
Armor comparable to Velious quest stuff, soloable - Nice touch no complaints<br>
<br>
Egress/Succor improvements (reduced mana, Lesser Succor)<br>
- This was not done to help us but rather done to get groups into the unused dungeons - I like the change alot - I just do not consider it directed as helping Druids<br>
<br>
Wildfire improvement (reduced cast time) - you call 0.2 (or something close to that) a big improvement?<br>
<br>
Our AA is not bad. - I cannot talk much as I only have 1 alt point. Looking at all the AA things nothing stuck out cept Dire Charm and after other classes got done "explaining" to Verant the spell was nerfed!<br>
<br>
In the last two expansions Druids got a VERY short end of the stick. Each and every class bitched about how good Druids were and this is the result. People even bitch about us asking to be looked at and you can sure as bet they will bitch if/when Verant does anything for us.<br>
<br>
If I hated my class so much I would not continue playing but not having an alt or the incentive to start one from scratch maybe it stinks more when other can switch out to a needed class for a raid when their Druid is not needed and I have to either go on the raid as window dressing or go solo somewhere :)<br>
<br>
Any thoughts to the fact that many of these spells ROTG ROTG ROTG ROTG ROTG are so damn rare? Verant knows we are DYING for help with healing and a good portion of level 60 Druids STILL do not have this MUCH needed level 58 spell.<br>
<br>
